<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-17T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-17T03:00:00-05:00" n="396" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d396">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5151/944: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi>, (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-17T15:00:00+07:00">July 17,
                                    1943—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 20—1:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1211. State Department’s 882, July 9, part I. In accordance with your
                            suggestion, [I] took the opportunity during a call on Dr. Kung on the
                            15th to have an informal discussion with him to make sure that he fully
                            understands the Treasury position with respect to revision of 1941
                            Agreement. He gave the impression—I think deliberately—that China was
                            not particularly anxious to have a stabilization loan; presumably this
                            is largely jockeying for bargaining position. At the same time he
                            intimated that China would ask for certain specific changes in 1941
                            Agreement without indicating what they would be.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>